1 2. One member appointed by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
2 Representatives, who shall be a citizen from a county with a
3 population under twenty-five thousand (25,000) persons, as
4 determined by the latest Federal Decennial Census;
5 3. One member appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the
6 Oklahoma State Senate, who shall be a citizen from a municipality
7 with a population in excess of seventy-five thousand (75,000)
8 persons, as determined by the latest Federal Decennial Census;
9 4. One member appointed by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
10 Representatives, who is a current medical marijuana business license
11 holder;
12 5. One member appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the
13 Oklahoma State Senate, who is a current medical marijuana business
14 license holder; and
15 6. One member appointed by the Governor, who holds a medical
16 marijuana patient license.
17 C. The Executive Director of the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana
18 Authority shall chair the Advisory Council and provide staff and
19 administrative support to the Advisory Council.
20 D. The Advisory Council shall select a co-chair from the
21 membership of the Advisory Council.
22 E. Each member of the Advisory Council shall serve a term of
23 four (4) years from the date of appointment. Members of the
24 Advisory Council shall not serve more than two consecutive terms.
