1 F. A majority of the members of the Advisory Council shall
2 constitute a quorum for the transaction of business and for taking
3 any official actions. Official actions by the Advisory Council
4 shall have a favorable vote by a majority of the members present.
5 G. Appointed members who serve on the Advisory Council shall be
6 exempt from dual-office-holding prohibitions pursuant to Section 6
7 of Title 51 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
8 H. The Advisory Council may advise the Authority of recommended
9 changes to state policy, rules, or statutes.
10 I. The Advisory Council shall organize a task force to research
11 and provide recommendations on purchase and possession limits for
12 licensed medical marijuana patients. This task force shall consult
13 with various professionals and stakeholders including, but not
14 limited to, physicians, the State Board of Medical Licensure and
15 Supervision, the State Board of Osteopathic Examiners, the Board of
16 Podiatric Medical Examiners, licensed medical marijuana patients,
17 veterans, and licensed medical marijuana business owners. The task
18 force may meet separately from the Advisory Council and as often as
19 necessary to conduct business. The task force shall submit a final
20 report of its findings and recommendations to the Authority by
21 November 1, 2026.
22 J. The Advisory Council shall prepare and issue a report of its
23 findings and recommendations electronically to the Governor,
24 President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and Speaker of the House by
